== Blue Teaming Synthesis

This chapter's central result is that robust blue teaming is a control system, not a static control list. Effective defense emerges from the interaction of input constraints, data governance, model safeguards, execution controls, and operational response.

Research gap note: many practitioner frameworks enumerate controls, but fewer provide explicit mechanisms to connect those controls to adversarial test evidence over time. The integration approach in this thesis addresses that gap by binding each control layer to measurable outcomes and regression testing.

Threats-to-validity note: control efficacy can vary across model families, deployment contexts, and attacker adaptation speed. For this reason, all blue-team claims in this paper are treated as conditional and continuously re-evaluable.
